Topic: What have we seen, heard, and read so far?

Question Text: What have you learned from this unit?

Question Language: English

Setting: The classroom SYLLABUS 1.3 Unit One hour, Five days KNOWLEDGE Standard 1.2: Recognization and Promotion of Rights and Responsibilities - National and International

Standard 1.4: Maintenance and Blackline Master 5.1 How often do we use our school's library for independent or group work?

MAIN LESSON Objective: The main objective of this lesson is for the students to recognize and explain the school hours and closer of public university and private school.

Materials: File Folder with cut out pictures and description of pictures, Notecard holders

Time Frame: 2 hours (15 min. break)

PROTOCOL (Teacher and Student Actions) GROUP INSTRUCTION Teach the learning strategy of group work (How will you work with your groups, rules of engagement, actions?) discussed below.

Discuss and review the new content with the students (What is it we are going to learn?)

Review the teacher demonstration, using individually selected, relevant and important vocabulary and concepts related to Module Learning Objectives as appropriate.

Engage with students through inquiry teaching, acknowledging students
